rComments: Lectures are boring, she has no patience for a 150 student class and essentially reads off the slides so get that textbook and START READING.

She gives you a table to fill out for both assignments, which most people would use as an indicator to estimate how much to write. But then you get your marks back and you basically failed because the TA was "looking for more". Ok great MAYBE BE MORE CLEAR NEXT TIME

I found her class interesting and engaging. The content presented was clear. No midterm so thats a plus. However, the pop quizzes were a killer. So make sure to study ahead of time. Two assignments which were pretty easy. Overall, she's a caring prof, she does want you to do well and is willing to help you.

The content is fairly easy but the assignments killed my marks. The criteria wasn't clear, she posted the syllabus hours before one of the assignments so ask for it ahead of time. She makes you do jumping jacks in every 30 mins in a 2 hr lec. Don't waste your money on the textbook, she covers everything in lecture. Know the concepts well for final
